18 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
19 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
20 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6-195.3 of Title 70, unless
21 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
22 A. An individual employed for the first time in the state as a
23 district superintendent shall complete the professional development
24 requirements provided for in subsection B of this section within the
Req. No. 12283 Page 1

1 firs t year of employment as a district superintendent to maintain a
2 provisional or standard school superintendent certification. If the
3 individual fails to complete the professional development
4 requirements as provided for in this section, the individual's
5 superintendent certification shall be considered invalid and the
6 Oklahoma State Board of Education shall revoke the individual's
7 superintendent certificate.
8 B. During an individual's first year of employment as a
9 superintendent, the individual shall attend professional development
10 workshops or training seminars equal to sixty-six (66) hours of
11 training in areas that include, but are not limited to, the
12 following:
13 1. Superintendent and board of education relationships;
14 2. Legal issues, school law, and the Oklahoma Open Meeting Act;
15 3. Staff relationships;
16 4. Community relationships;
17 5. School finance;
18 6. Plant management and school facilities;
19 7. Setting school district and site goals; and
20 8. Individuals with Disabilities Education Act.
21 C. The professional development workshops or training seminars
22 for a first-year superintendent shall be determined by the local
23 school district based on the training areas and hours identified in
24 subsection B of this section. The local school district shall issue
